            ------
            Download: As a Maven module or source code
            ------
 

Maven module

  AnnoCultor can be used as a Maven module, so that the latest release is
  always automatically downloaded and used.
  
  To use AnnoCultor as a Maven module you first need to create a Maven project.
  Please, refer to {{{http://maven.apache.org} Maven project site}} to learn what 
  Maven is and how you can benefit from it.
  
  Then, you need to modify your <<<pom.xml>>> file with the following 
  two fragments.
  
  Set your project to use the AnnoCultor Maven repository:
  
+------------------------------------------------------------------+
 <repositories>
	...
	<repository>
		<id>annocultor.eu</id>
		<name>AnnoCultor</name>
		<url>http://annocultor.eu/repository/maven2/</url>
		<releases>
			<enabled>true</enabled>
  			<updatePolicy>always</updatePolicy>
		</releases>
	</repository>
  ...
 </repositories>
+------------------------------------------------------------------+
  
  Add AnnoCultor as a Maven dependency:
   
+------------------------------------------------------------------+
 <dependencies>
	...
	<dependency>
		<groupId>annocultor</groupId>
		<artifactId>annocultor</artifactId>
		<version>RELEASE</version>
	</dependency>
	...
 </dependencies>		
+------------------------------------------------------------------+
  
